Analysis of Main Target Image  
• Block Count & Layers:  
  – There are 4 total pieces arranged in 3 layers.  
     1. Bottom layer: a single red arch block.  
     2. Middle layer: two yellow half‐cylinder blocks, side by side.  
     3. Top layer: a single orange triangular “roof” block.  

• Spatial Relationships:  
  – The red arch is on the ground layer with its curved opening at the bottom center.  
  – Directly on top of the arch, two yellow half‐cylinders lie next to each other, forming a “full circle” shape when viewed from the front.  
  – An orange triangular wedge sits atop those half‐cylinders, completing the “house” roof shape.  

Selection of Required Blocks from Dictionary  
• Red Arch (bottom): Block #1 (1 copy)  
• Yellow Half‐Cylinders (middle): Block #6 (2 copies)  
• Orange Triangular “Roof” (top): Block #16 (1 copy)  

Assembly Order  
{  
  Step1: Move block with index 1  
  Step2: Move block with index 6  
  Step3: Move block with index 6  
  Step4: Move block with index 16
